entry.content:
This CL introduces BluetoothChooserIOS and BluetoothDeviceList

and supports a basic functionality for choosing a bluetooth device.



BluetoothChooserIOS has BluetoothDeviceList that holds UITableView

to manage a device list. UITableView is loaded as a popover and a

device is added to UITableView or updated when

BluetoothChooserIOS::AddOrUpdateDevice() is called.

entry.title: [omnibox][doc] Display shorter URLs.
entry.content:
https://screenshot.googleplex.com/7ReyxdCrmUns4Dj



The remote doc response contains 2 URLs per document: `originalUrl` and

`url`.

- `originalUrl` is much shorter. E.g.

https://drive.google.com/a/google.com/open?id=&resourcekey=



- `url` is much longer. E.g.,

https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&rct=j&esrc=s&source=

appssearch&uact=8&cd=0&cad=rja&q=&sig2=9NB3hPvQWP_8Z-

OMFJTsog&ved=0ahUKEwiB3e6Z_Ov-AhXxEvkAHZhmB0k4ABABKAAwAA&url

=https://drive.google.com/a/google.com/open%3Fid%3D

%26resourcekey%3D&usg=AOvVaw2q5Vrrjd92EfjX5jek6uxD



Currently,

- navigating (i.e. `destination_url`) uses the longer `url`.

- omnibox display (i.e. `fill_into_edit`) uses the longer `url`

- deduping (i.e. `stripped_destination_url`) uses the shorter

`originalUrl`.



With this CL, display will use the shorter `originalUrl`. Navigation

will continue to use `url`.



This allows copying doc URLs without having to navigate to them and wait

for the redirects to complete. Though the redirected final URL still

differs from the `originalUrl`.



This CL also has the `stripped_destination_url` fallback to use `url`

when `originalUrl` is empty.

entry.title: [fuchsia] Ensure services are not unintentionally offered from host component
entry.content:
Previously, CreateInstanceForContextWithCopiedArgs() would offer

services from the current Component, the `web_instance` host, iff no

`service_directory` was provided in the provided `CreateContextParams`.

This could lead to mistakes, like the one fixed by

https://crrev.com/c/4528805, or even abuse if no `service_directory`

or a partial `service_directory` was provided. Since the two modes are

for very different use cases, split them out into separate

sub-classes.

entry.title: Clean up PrintContext::ComputePageRects().
entry.content:
Make ComputePageRects() private and non-virtual, and only call it from

BeginPrintMode(). No need to trust call sites to follow up a call to

BeginPrintMode() with a call ComputePageRects() with the correct size.



Remove ComputePageRectsWithPageSize().



printing/css2.1/page-break-inside-000.html now passes also in highdpi,

now that PrintContext::PageNumberForElement() no longer calculates the

page rectangles in its own special way.

entry.content:
Adds special handling for some net::Error codes.



net::ERR_INVALID_WEB_BUNDLE: when the swbn file has been removed or no

longer valid.



net::ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED: when dev-proxy server cannot be reached.



All other net::Error will be displayed as net::ERR_XXX.



HTTP status errors will have their net::Error set as

ERR_HTTP_RESPONSE_CODE_FAILURE, they will be directed to use default

error page at a higher level. This means for the moment,

MaybeGetIsolatedWebAppErrorPageInfo can not encounter

ERR_HTTP_RESPONSE_CODE_FAILURE. IWA will continue to use default error

page for HTTP status errors.

entry.title: [Extensions] Use browser context unique id in extension utils
entry.content:
Previously, extensions util generated a "unique id" given a browser

context and stored them in a `std::map`. This was problematic because if the BrowserContext gets

destroyed, another BrowserContext could be placed in the same address

and get the "unique id" of the destroyed BrowserContext.



Instead, we can use the BrowserContext::UniqueId that guarantees a

unique id. We maintain the map generated by extension utils because

the types are different (int vs string) and because it's also used by

the renderer.
